 ARCHITECTS' COMPETITION FOR THE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY LIBRARY.GUTERSLOH PUBLIC LIBRARY WAS FOUNDED IN 1979 AS A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY BYTHE MUNICIPAL COUNCIL AND THE FIRM OF BERTELSMANN. IN 1980, SINCE EXISTINGACCOMMODATION WAS TOO SMALL, AN ARCHITECTS' COMPETITION WAS HELD TO DESIGN ANEW LIBRARY BASED ON THE '3-TIER SYSTEM'. DETAILS ARE GIVEN OF THE TOP 5DESIGNS. THE WINNER HAS PLACED ON THE GROUND FLOOR A PASSAGE RUNNING RIGHTTHROUGH THE LIBRARY TO THE PARK BEYOND; OFF THIS PASSAGE IS THE '1ST TIER' OFPOPULAR FICTION AND NON-FICTION, ISSUE COUNTER AND READERS' CAFE WITHNEWSPAPERS. THE 1ST AND 2ND FLOORS HOUSE MORE FICTION, NON-FICTION ANDPERIODICALS; THE 2ND FLOOR ALSO HOUSES STUDY CARRELS, MEDIA CENTRE, CONFERENCEROOM, STACK, ART CENTRE AND OFFICES. THE ADMINISTRATION SECTION IS ON THE 3RDFLOOR AND THE CHILDREN'S LIBRARY ON THE LOWER GROUND FLOOR